# Old World Tech Homebrew — Project Rules

This repository is **fan homebrew** for **Cyberpunk RED**: pre-Collapse **Old World** salvage, repurposing, and post-Collapse updates. All **content** is **Markdown** (`.md`).

## Legal and licensing

- Follow R. Talsorian’s **[Homebrew Content Policy](https://rtalsoriangames.com/homebrew-content-policy)**. Do not reproduce core rulebook **text**, stat blocks, or rulesets verbatim.
- The **README** carries the **required RTG disclaimer** and **CC0** notice for original material. Do not remove them.
- Original writing in this repo is **CC0**; that does **not** license Cyberpunk IP.

## README

- Keep the **README** high-level: premise, repository layout, spotlight content, disclaimer, license.
- **Repository layout** table: folders in **alphabetical order** by folder name (`ammo/`, `armor/`, …). **Do not** paste long field-by-field templates into the README.

## Folder categories

Use the existing top-level folders: `ammo/`, `armor/`, `clothing/`, `cyberwear/`, `gear/`, `vehicles/`, `weapons/`. Place new items in the correct category.

## Marks and economy (this homebrew line)

When an item uses **Mark I / II / III** progression, align **pricing** and **power** with this baseline unless the user specifies otherwise:

| Mark | Tier | Typical price (homebrew eb) |
|------|------|-----------------------------|
| **Mark I** | Early game | **550** |
| **Mark II** | Mid game | **1,250** |
| **Mark III** | Late game / legendary | **3,000** |

Mark III **glasses** in this line are **dock-only** (require the Mark III cranial implant in `cyberwear/`); do not treat them like standalone powered gear.

## Gear documents (`gear/`)

Structure (match existing AR glasses pattern unless the user asks otherwise):

- **Title** with mark and variant name (e.g. role-specific or **Generic**).
- **Short description** line.
- Optional intro line for **Generic** (baseline vs role-tuned).
- **`## Description`** — long description; **Cost** at the **end** of the description block (before custom modifiers).
- **`## Custom Modifiers`** — bullet list of bonuses.

Use **role-tuned** files for each Cyberpunk RED role where it fits; use **Alternate** files when a different **primary stat** fits the same role (pattern: `*-exec-alternate.md`, `*-netrunner-alternate.md`, `*-media-alternate.md`).

**Filenames:** kebab-case; include `-mark-i`, `-mark-ii`, or `-mark-iii` as appropriate.

## Armor documents (`armor/`)

Aligned with **Cyberpunk RED Companion**-style fields. **Order:**

1. **Name** — `#` title (include **Mark I / II / III** in the name when the line uses marks).
2. **Short description**
3. **`Armor:`** — exactly one value: **Head**, **Body**, **Shield**, **Head and Body**, or **Assisted combat / power armor**
4. **`Stopping power — Current:`** and **`Stopping power — Max:`** — only these two numbers (no per-location SP tables in the template).
5. **`Armor penalty:`** — numeric / none as appropriate for the item.
6. **`## Long description`** — fiction and behavior; at the **end** of this section, add an **`Appearance:`** paragraph (what it looks like: cut, color, hardware, wear), then **`Cost:`** on the last line(s) of the long-description section.
7. **`## Custom modifiers`** — bullets; use **None** when empty.

**Marks:** For layered lines (e.g. laminar-weave overcoat), use separate files per mark (`*-mark-i.md`, `*-mark-ii.md`, `*-mark-iii.md`) with stepped **SP** and prices matching the table above.

## Cyberware (`cyberwear/`)

- Include **Type**, **Install**, **Cost (eb)**, **Humanity Cost** where relevant.
- State **compatibility** with Mark I / II / III **gear** explicitly (e.g. charge tethers vs cranial dock).
- **Mark III cranial dock:** modifiers for the full rig live on **Mark III glasses** entries unless the user directs otherwise; the dock provides coupling and power narrative.

## Style

- Prefer **clear, professional** prose; avoid filler.
- Use **`cyberwear/`** folder name as in this repo (not “cyberware”) for paths.
- When citing this project’s files, use paths consistent with the repo (e.g. `gear/`, `armor/`, `cyberwear/`).
